‘A two metre increase in significant wave height over a decade led to a two degree latitudinal retreat in ice extent.’

Dr
 Kohout found that the largest increases in wave height occurred in the 
Amundsen-Bellingshausen Sea, where regional sea ice retreat is well 
documented.

Similarly, the largest wave height decreases were in the Western Ross Sea, where sea ice has expanded.

